race.comment: PANDA UNLEASHED (1) clocked a useful 22.93 when filling a minor placing over 400m at Dubbo last start. Has the ability and expected to go close again. MOTOR CITY CHIEF (5) jumps from box 5 for the first time after placing latest at this track (30.35) in a Grade 5. Has never missed the frame at the trip from five starts. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Leading player again. POKER NISMO (6) produced a moderate effort last time when eighth at Maitland over 450m behind Tarawi Lock (26.11) in a Grade 5. Scored at her previous run. The form out of last race has been strong. Has ability and can atone. LARNIE'S MAGIC (7) should be thereabouts despite an unplaced run here most recently.
